&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: helvetica, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;&quot;&gt;We believe our best work happens when we’re together. AV operates as a 5-day-a-week, in-office culture because collaboration, mentorship, and shared momentum matter.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: helvetica, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;About the Role&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: helvetica, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;&quot;&gt;At Alumni Ventures, we&#39;re always looking to connect with exceptional venture professionals who are passionate about discovering transformative companies and partnering with founders. As Principal, you&#39;ll be at the forefront of sourcing, evaluating, and executing investments for one of our investment teams, while also contributing across the broader Alumni Ventures platform.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: helvetica, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;&quot;&gt;This is an expression-of-interest opportunity designed to help us connect with exceptional venture professionals for future Principal-level opportunities across Alumni Ventures. While we may not be actively hiring for a specific opening at the time of application, we regularly review candidates for opportunities across our offices in New York City, Boston, Manchester (NH), Chicago, and Menlo Park. Applications will be reviewed on an ongoing basis and considered as relevant opportunities arise.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: helvetica, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;&quot;&gt;The role is fundamentally T-shaped. It is a generalist investing role spanning sectors and stages, with the opportunity to develop your own investment theses and areas of expertise. Our primary focus is Seed and Series A investing, while also participating in select Pre-Seed and Growth-stage opportunities. You&#39;ll help shape a portfolio of approximately 25 investments annually, identify follow-on opportunities, contribute to strong fund performance, and strengthen our position within the venture ecosystem.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: helvetica, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;&quot;&gt;You&#39;ll work closely with the Managing Partner, Senior Associates, and broader team to identify high-potential companies, lead diligence and negotiations, and cultivate relationships with founders, co-investors, and industry partners. Your network will be one of your greatest assets. Building trusted relationships with colleagues, venture investors, and founders to gain access to exceptional investment opportunities is essential. Success in this role comes from combining strong investment judgment, intellectual curiosity, creativity, warmth, and sound decision-making.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
